      "message": "[warning] Line 374: The `pingPush` retry is registered with `start` instead of `safeStart`, so it bypasses the `currentCalls.containsKey(id)` stale-call guard when the retry runs later. If the call ends before push wake-up retries the foreground service start, this can still start `CallNotificationService` for a disconnected call. Register the guarded action for delayed retry, and keep rollback behavior inside that path. For example:\n```suggestion\n                                pingPush(conference.accountId) { safeStart() }\n```",
